# InterMUN Figma-First UI Rule

Use the provided Figma system as the source of truth for UI work.

## File / Page Structure (Figma)
- Keep the 4-page structure in mind for all design decisions:
  - `01 — Foundations`
  - `02 — Components`
  - `03 — Patterns (Screens)`
  - `04 — Prototypes`

## Foundations
- Respect base color intents:
  - `bg/primary #0B0B0F`, `bg/secondary #12121A`, `bg/glass rgba(255,255,255,0.04)`
  - `text/primary #FFFFFF`, `text/secondary #B3B3B3`, `text/muted #6B6B6B`
  - `accent/primary #1DB954`, `accent/warm #C2A878`, `accent/danger #FF5A5F`
- Respect typography intents:
  - UI Sans for app chrome (`h1/h2/body`)
  - Serif for document surfaces
  - Mono for system metadata
- Use 8pt spacing rhythm: `4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48`.
- Reuse glass/shadow patterns:
  - Glass card feel with subtle stroke + blur
  - Soft shadow depth

## Components and Naming
- Keep existing naming and structural semantics intact.
- Build and evolve UI using the specified component families:
  - Sidebar, Top Bar, Card, Dashboard Panel, Live Session Bar, Committees Card
  - Documents (Clause Item / Editor / Toolbar)
  - Messages Thread, Voting Button / Results Bar
  - Chair Controls (Speakers List / Motion Button)
  - Profile Header / Stats, Admin Table

## Patterns
- Compose screens from reusable components (Dashboard, Committees, Documents, Voting, Chair Controls).
- Prefer consistency and reuse over one-off page-specific styling.

## Auto Layout / Layout Behavior
- Apply auto-layout principles in implementation:
  - vertical page flow
  - internal spacing around `16–24`
  - inter-element gaps around `12–16`
- Keep sidebar fixed and main content fill behavior.

## Strict Constraint
- Enhance UI only through:
  - color
  - texture
  - motion
- Do **not** change:
  - labels
  - information architecture / structural naming
